<subSubSection id="5EDA654AFFFBFFCFEA9F4CEAFD1DF927" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="167F36C1FFFBFFCFEA9F4CEAFEA6FA3B" blockId="7.[192,605,1394,1457]" box="[192,303,1430,1457]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
(
<figureCitation id="8EFB2A44FFFBFFCFEA984CEAFEAFFA3B" box="[199,294,1430,1457]" captionStart="Figures 1–9" captionStartId="4.[192,279,831,857]" captionTargetBox="[243,1383,223,792]" captionTargetId="figure-449@4.[240,1392,213,801]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 1–9. Dorsal and ventral habitus of adult Chrysina specimens (1×). 1–2) C. clavellina Holotype male. 3–4) C. clavellina female. 5) C. lacordairei. 6) C. adelaida red morph. 7) C. adelaida green morph. 8) C. expansa. 9) C. adolphi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565329" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565329/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Figure 8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="167F36C1FFFBFFCFEB5F4CB4FD1DF927" blockId="7.[191,1441,1480,1709]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
This is a little-known species of 
<taxonomicName id="D1C04D42FFFBFFCFE83D4CB4FD4FFA68" authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1828" box="[610,710,1480,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Chrysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24B4EAD3FFFBFFCFE83D4CB4FD4FFA68" box="[610,710,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Chrysina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has been collected only at a few localities in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="D404F823FFFBFFCFEF384CB4FF6EF98F" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
. It has been found in forests dominated by oak trees (
<taxonomicName id="D1C04D42FFFBFFCFE91B4C97FC16F98F" box="[836,927,1515,1541]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24B4EAD3FFFBFFCFE91B4C97FC16F98F" box="[836,927,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species) at elevations between 2000 and 2300 meters above sea level. Specimens were found in the vicinity of Santiago Clavellinas at elevations between 2100 and 
<quantity id="D1389B24FFFBFFCFEAAE4F52FECDF9C2" box="[241,324,1582,1608]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="2300.0">2300 m</quantity>
in pine-oak forests (Five males and five females) during August–September 2018 and 
<date id="627E1001FFFBFFCFEEA04F52FAE3F9C2" box="[1279,1386,1582,1608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" value="2019-07">July 2019</date>
. Our recent discovery of this species in the Sierra Azul represents an interesting new locality record. Ongoing research by Blackaller and Hawks will provide additional information on 
<taxonomicName id="D1C04D42FFFBFFCFE9C64F0EFB9BF901" baseAuthorityName="Ohaus" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[921,1042,1650,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Chrysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis id="24B4EAD3FFFBFFCFE9C64F0EFB9BF901" box="[921,1042,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">C. expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other closely related species in the Peruviana Group (
<emphasis id="24B4EAD3FFFBFFCFEBE54FE8FE7FF927" box="[442,502,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="72514B30FFFBFFCFEBA34FEFFD01F927" author="Hawks DC" box="[508,648,1683,1709]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref4034" refString="Hawks DC. 2001. Taxonomic and nomenclatural changes in Chrysina and a synonymic checklist of species (Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae). Occasional Papers of the Consortium Coleopterorum 4: 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2001">Hawks 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
